<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-346-976  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 346 976.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  April 16 1990 n296 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>MCI bids $1.25B for foe. (plans to purchase Telecom USA LongDistance Co. for $1.25 billion) (MCI Communications Corp.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Schultz, Beth.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>MCI Communications Corp announces its bid of $1.25 billion toacquire Telecom*USA Long Distance Co. If the deal is approved byregulators, MCI will gain the competitor's 500,000 customersspread across 31 states, as well as its 3,000 mile fiber opticnetwork.andP;  The purchase would also bolster MCI's presence in thesmall business market and give it Telecom*USA's record ofinnovative products.andP;  Analysts, while agreeing that theshort-range effect of the acquisition strategy would be improvedservice and competitive prices, were concerned about its long termeffects.andP;  With Telecom*USA out of the picture, it was pointed out,a three-player oligopoly could develop in which AT and T, USSprint Communications Co and MCI would have no serious competitionin the long distance arena.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   MCI Communications Corp. (acquisitions and mergers)Telecom*USA Inc. (acquisitions and mergers).andO;Ticker:    MCIC.andO;Topic:     AcquisitionCompetitionTelecommunicationsFiber OpticsStrategic PlanningMergerCommunications Industry.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>